An NGO, Mcray Victus Foundation, has donated food items, as well as paid school fees for orphans of Anawim Orphanage in Gwagwalada Area Council of the FCT. The chairman of the foundation, Mr Innocent Unaji, while presenting the food items and cash donations at the orphanage on Sunday, said the gesture was to assist the orphans and other less privileged. ‘Stop the Flooding Campaign’ commences in Abuja ‘FCT school feeding will be sustained despite rising cost of foodstuff’ Among the items donated were bags of rice, spaghetti, noodles, Maggi, salt, sugar, tin tomato, vegetable oil, garri and toiletries.